"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-lewis-richardson-boxing-bronze-team-gb-b1175075.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  Team GB'sLewis Richardsonhopes he can \\\"flick the switch\\\" and be proud of hisboxingbronze medal success at theOlympicsin the not too distant future.  The 27-year-old fell narrowly short of reaching the men's 71kg gold medal match after being beaten on split decision by Mexico's Marco Verde in the semi-final at Roland Garros on Tuesday.  Bronze means Richardson is the only British boxer at Paris 2024 to win a medal. He was already guaranteed bronze following victory against Zeyad Eashash in the quarter-finals on Saturday and reflected on a bittersweet feeling after missing the chance to go for gold.  He said: \\\"It's very raw and it is hard to process right now. I have won that bronze medal, but it's hard to fully celebrate because you are moving onto the next one and looking to change the colour of that medal.  \\\"I am sure I am going to make a conscious effort whenever the time's right - and hopefully sooner rather than later - to flick that switch and be proud of what I have achieved.  \\\"Because rightly or wrongly, I am the only British boxer to medal at these Games and I hope I have made the country proud.\\\"  Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions  Incredible days out and trips for autumn and winter  Richardson started the semi-final well, landing a solid punch to Verde's face, but the Mexican grew back into the round throwing a series of different combinations and breaking through the British fighter's defence.  The second round saw the British fighter show off his skills, landing a great uppercut and a couple of big blows to Verde's head to take the round on the majority of the judges' cards.  An evenly-poised contest boiled down to the third round and Richardson began to use his reach more, throwing a big strike to Verde's nose.  The Mexican caught the British fighter on the cheek but struggled to land some big swings before being hit in the face again by Richardson.  However, all five judges saw it differently and awarded the Mexican the round which meant Richardson's dream of reaching the Olympic final was over and he admitted afterwards that he felt he won what was a tight contest.  He added: \\\"It was close, it was a close bout. It's hard to say really if I am happy, I am a bit disappointed with my performance but what I will say is I am proud of myself about how I have conducted myself throughout this tournament.  \\\"I have been ultra-professional and I hope that I have represented the country with pride and honour because I have done my best.  \\\"So I hope the country are happy and proud of what I have achieved because although I have lost tonight I have managed to bring a bronze medal home.  \\\"I certainly did feel like I won the bout, but I am certainly not screaming a robbery because it's close and it's far too soon to say anything like that.  \\\"For me he was a good opponent, seeded number two in the tournament and I am happy with my performances this week.\\\"  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"